headline: CDNS Q2 Deep Dive: AI Demand and Product Expansion Drive Upbeat Outlook
summary: Semiconductor design software provider Cadence Design Systems (NASDAQ:CDNS) reported Q2 CY2025 results beating Wall Street’s revenue expectations, with sales up 20.2% year on year to $1.28 billion. The company’s full-year revenue guidance of $5.24 billion at the midpoint came in 0.8% above analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.65 per share was 5.9% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
